          "tz": 180
        },
        "subject": "LU-110 Old-style quota type handling fix",
        "message": "LU-110 Old-style quota type handling fix\n\nVersion 1.8 uses a tunable named \"mdt.quota_type\" in order to store\nquota parameters in config, while version 2.x has a tunable named\n\"mdd.quota_type\" for the same purpose. This introduces incompatibility\nwhen trying to run a 2.x Lustre instance on top of a filesystem with a\n1.8 disk format.\n\nChange-Id: I5176c19d1047101650d638a1a0596d091e8cf1d6\nSigned-off-by: Alexey Lyashkov <Alexey_Lyashkov@xyratex.com>\nSigned-off-by: Vitaly Fertman <vitaly_fertman@xyratex.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
